    "duration_s": 45.0773125,
    "text": "Yesterday, we were able to get a recording from him and we had a colleague and comrade translate for us. So this is from Juan. Good morning, I was released Friday the 24th of April. I was detained for three months at North Lake, 90 days. The conditions right now are very upsetting because ICE is not following regulations complying with the law. By which I mean certain judges are not following the laws and are trying to do what they want instead. The federal judges want to make decisions on their own terms. They are issuing very high bond awards as well as denials of bond in asylum cases, for example. I ended up being detained at North Lake because of ICE. They didn't respect the law because I had a-",
